Interface DirectoryEntry

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Comparable<DirectoryEntry>
    All Known Subinterfaces:

    public interface DirectoryEntry
extends Comparable<DirectoryEntry>
    An entry in a Directory representing a file or sub-directory.

    Donal Fellows

    Directory, File

    • Method Detail

      • getName

        String getName()
        Returns:
        The "local" name of the entry. This will never be ".." or contain the character "/".

      • getFullName

        String getFullName()
        Returns:
        The "full" name of the entry. This is computed relative to the workflow run's working directory. It may contain the "/" character.

      • getModificationDate

        Date getModificationDate()
        Returns:
        The time that the entry was last modified.

      • destroy

        void destroy()
      throws FilesystemAccessException
        Destroy this directory entry, deleting the file or sub-directory. The workflow run's working directory can never be manually destroyed.
        Throws:
        FilesystemAccessException - If the destroy fails for some reason.
